        HOME B4 THE STRAITS TIMES THURSDAY, SEPTEMBER 24, 2020 | | | ● A monthly video series organised by
The Straits Times and the National Library Board you ask, we answer, come listen How to stay sane in the Covid-19 economic downturn Joyce Teo The Straits Times’ senior health correspond­ent hosts a mindfulnes­s expert and founder of the Brahm Centre, a charity where people can get health education as well as emotional and mental support. She was named The Straits Times Singaporea­n of The Year 2019 for her advocacy of mental wellness. Ms Angie Chew, The Covid-19 pandemic has severely impacted the Singapore economy, and, in the coming months, business closures, retrenchme­nts and unemployme­nt are expected to go up. Ms Chew offers insights on how you can reframe your thinking to prepare yourself for the changes that may come in this pandemic, and emerge stronger, more resilient and more positive. Watch the video The Straits Times Facebook Friday, Sept 25, 7pm Joyce Teo Angie Chew Senior Health Correspond­ent The Straits Times Founder Brahm Centre PRINTED AND DISTRIBUTE­D BY PRESSREADE­R PressReade­r.com +1 604 278 4604 ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY . ORIGINAL COPY COPYRIGHT AND PROTECTED BY APPLICABLE LAW
